        <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Track your parts usage monthly. Top techs adjust their inventory based on actual call data, not guesswork. If you're replacing more 40 MFD capacitors than 35 MFD, stock accordingly.</p>

        <h3>Secondary Parts (Stock After Core Inventory)</h3>

        <p>Once your core inventory is dialed in, add these components that handle another 15% of service calls:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Relays and Timers:</strong> Fan relays, time delay relays, defrost timers ($280-$350 investment)</li>
          <li><strong>Motors and Blowers:</strong> Common condenser fan motors, blower wheels ($650-$900)</li>
          <li><strong>Control Boards:</strong> 2-3 universal boards for common brands ($320-$480)</li>
          <li><strong>Electrical Components:</strong> Wire nuts, electrical tape, disconnect switches ($150-$200)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="truck-organization">Organization Systems</h2>

        <p>Organization isn't about looking neat, it's about speed. The average tech spends 18 minutes per service call looking for parts and tools. Top performers cut this to 6 minutes through systematic organization.</p>

        <h3>Proven Organization Approaches</h3>

        <p><strong>Zone-Based System (Most Popular):</strong> Divide your truck into 5 zones:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Hot Zone (Driver Side, Easy Access):</strong> Most common parts (capacitors, fuses, filters)</li>
          <li><strong>Electrical Zone:</strong> All electrical components and meters</li>
          <li><strong>Refrigeration Zone:</strong> Gauges, refrigerant, leak detectors</li>
          <li><strong>Hardware Zone:</strong> Screws, brackets, mounting hardware</li>
          <li><strong>Specialty Zone:</strong> Less common parts and seasonal items</li>
        </ol>

        <p><strong>Modular Drawer System:</strong> 78% of top performers use modular drawer systems. Leading options include:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Weather Guard Model 664-52:</strong> $2,400-$2,800 (8 drawers, 2,000 lb capacity)</li>
          <li><strong>Knaack Model 89:</strong> $1,900-$2,200 (6 drawers, weather resistant)</li>
          <li><strong>Adrian Steel #4VFD:</strong> $2,100-$2,500 (customizable, ford transit specific)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Return on investment for quality organization systems averages 4.2 months through reduced search time and fewer return trips.</p>

        <h3>Labeling and Inventory Control</h3>

        <p>Smart labeling reduces part location time by 65%. Winning approaches include:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Color-coded labels:</strong> Red for electrical, blue for refrigeration, green for hardware</li>
          <li><strong>QR code inventory:</strong> Link to digital inventory sheets (updated via smartphone)</li>
          <li><strong>Bin numbering system:</strong> Each compartment numbered, matched to inventory app</li>
        </ul>

