        <h2 id="seasonal-adjustments">Seasonal Adjustments</h2>

        <p>Smart techs adjust their truck setup seasonally to match demand patterns. This optimization can improve first-call completion rates from 89% to 96%.</p>

        <h3>Summer Setup (May-September)</h3>

        <p><strong>Inventory Focus (60% cooling, 25% electrical, 15% general):</strong></p>

        <ul>
          <li>Increase capacitor stock by 40% (especially 35-45 MFD range)</li>
          <li>Add extra R-410A refrigerant (3-4 bottles vs. 2 bottles off-season)</li>
          <li>Stock more condenser fan motors and contactors</li>
          <li>Carry additional air filters (customers more conscious during peak usage)</li>
          <li>Add emergency thermostats for weekend calls</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Winter Setup (November-March)</h3>

        <p><strong>Inventory Focus (70% heating, 20% electrical, 10% general):</strong></p>

        <ul>
          <li>Stock more ignitors and flame sensors</li>
          <li>Increase pressure switch and limit switch inventory</li>
          <li>Carry extra furnace filters and humidifier pads</li>
          <li>Add gas valve and heat exchanger inspection tools</li>
          <li>Stock emergency heating elements for heat pump backup</li>
        </ul>

